-- Dubai's Emaar says institutional tranche of malls unit IPO covered across range
-- By David French
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 11:36AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 15 (Reuters) - Emaar Properties <EMAR.DU> said the tranche of its malls unit initial share sale that was earmarked for institutional investors has been covered throughout the potential price range.

The Dubai-based developer is hoping to raise up to 5.8 billion dirhams ($1.58 billion) from the sale of 15.4 percent of the unit, whose assets include Dubai Mall, one of the world's largest shopping centres. [ID:nL6N0RF01V]